        <num>CC 2338</num>
        <heading>2338.  Community property</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2338.  Community property.
The community property comprises: property acquired during the existence of the legal regime through the effort, skill, or industry of either spouse; property acquired with community things or with community and separate things, unless classified as separate property under Article 2341; property donated to the spouses jointly; natural and civil fruits of community property; damages awarded for loss or injury to a thing belonging to the community; and all other property not classified by law as separate property.</p>
        </content>
